  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>heritage tomatoes</strong> in half and add them to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12 min or until the tomatoes are beginning to soften, then remove from the oven and set aside</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tomatoes are in the oven, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a separate baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, peel and finely slice the<strong> red onions</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of<strong> butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced red onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 2 min</p><p>Reduce the heat to low and cook for a further 8-10 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, unroll the <strong>puff pastry</strong> and cut it into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> squares</p><p>Transfer the <strong>pastry squares</strong> to a sheet of <strong>non-stick baking paper </strong>(the size of a baking tray!)</p><p>Score a 1cm border around the edge of the pastry with a knife</p><p>Prick the inside of the border all over with a fork (this will stop you getting a soggy bottom!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onions are caramelised, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and cook for 1-2 min further until all the vinegar has absorbed into the onion – these are your <strong>caramelised onions</strong></p><p>Remove the <strong>roasted tomatoes </strong>from the baking tray and set aside, reserving the tray</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pastry squares</strong> to the reserved baking tray</p><p>Top the centre of <strong>pastry squares</strong> with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>caramelised onion</strong> and <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the pastry is golden and crisp and the edges have puffed up – these are your<strong> tomato & caramelised onion tarts</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tarts are in the oven, combine the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2114.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> tomato & caramelised onion tarts</strong> with the <strong>crispy potatoes</strong> and <strong>rocket </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>salad</strong> with the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> <strong>dressing</strong> and garnish the tarts with the<strong> chopped basil</strong> and a grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
